ticket.original-body:
Consider the following route: map.detail "subscription_plans/:provider/:plan", :action => "detail", :requirements => {:plan => /[^ ]+/}
I want this route to match any string _without_ a space character. So "Telfort-100" matches "Telfort 100" does not. This however does not work. It matches both.
I believed this to be correct but it's not. Including anchors ('\A' '$' etc) is not allowed and the docs seem to suggest they are implicit.

